  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Is there any Indian on Quora who did MS,MBA in USA but did not get a job after completion of course and had to return to India?",
  "response": "It's possible to find individuals on Quora who have shared experiences similar to what you described\u2014Indian students who pursued MS or MBA degrees in the USA but did not secure employment and had to return to India. However, as of my last update, I don't have access to real-time data or specific user stories from Quora.\n\nTo find such stories, you can follow these steps on Quora:\n\n1. **Search Specific Queries**: Use search terms like \"Indian student MS USA no job,\" \"Indian MBA USA returned to India,\" or \"MS in USA and couldn't find a job.\"\n\n2. **Browse Through Answers**: Look for answers from users who identify themselves as having gone through this experience. Quora often has detailed personal accounts that can provide insights into the challenges faced.\n\n3. **Check Follow-Up Comments**: Sometimes, more detailed information or updated situations are shared in the comments section of the answers.\n\n4. **Quora Spaces and Topics**: Engage with spaces or topics related to Indian students in the USA, career advice, or specific educational experiences. These can be good sources for relevant discussions.\n\n5. **Follow Relevant Users**: If you find users who have shared similar experiences, following them might lead you to more detailed posts or updates about their situations.\n\nRemember, individual experiences can vary widely based on many factors including field of study, networking efforts, job market conditions at the time of graduation, visa issues, and personal circumstances. If you're researching for personal decision-making, consider a wide range of experiences and possibly consult with career services at universities or professional career counselors.",
